# Blockera-Only Scope

The primary project is the Blockera WordPress plugin at `wp-content/plugins/blockera/`.

## In scope

- All plugin source, tests, configs, and tooling under `wp-content/plugins/blockera/`
- Read-only reference inside Blockera: `source-code-block-editor/`, `source-code-wordpress/`

## Out of scope

Do not read, edit, search, stage, or run commands against:

- Other plugins in `wp-content/plugins/` (e.g. `blockera-pro`, `blockera-demo-*`, `akismet`)
- `wp-content/themes/` and unrelated site files

## Required behavior

- Limit searches, reads, and edits to `wp-content/plugins/blockera/**`
- Stage only Blockera paths in commits unless the user explicitly expands scope
- If a task needs an out-of-scope path, ask before proceeding
- Apply the same scope to subagents and parallel tasks

Run the `blockera-only` command at session start to reinforce this scope.
